g.text: Slug Line
The actual slug cut line.
Safe Zone
DO NOT place ANY important text, images, or cut
lines beyond this dotted line. Anything past the
dotted line has the potential for being trimmed.
This line is provided to prevent trimming of your
designs.
Nicks
To prevent cut pieces from falling out of slug, all
cut lines must have at least 3 “nicks”. A nick is
a break in the cut line that keeps the piece
attached to the slug. The recommended nick size
is .01” or .25mm. Any pieces without nicks make
fall out of slug and lost.
• All cut lines must be at least 1/8” apart.
• Line thickness does not affect the cut line. Lines
will be cut only down the center of any vector/line.
• Having lines cross could result in pieces becoming
disconnected.
• Check for duplicate vectors/lines directly on top of
each other. Duplicate lines can result in a line
being cut twice which can affect edge quality and
size.
